==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sepulture
<hw>Sep"ul*ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>s⟦eacute⟧pulture</ets>, L. <ets>sepultura</ets>, fr.
<ets>sepelire</ets>, <ets>sepultum</ets>, to bury.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of depositing the dead body of a human being in the grave;
burial; interment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where we may royal <qex>sepulture</qex> prepare.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sepulcher; a grave; a place of burial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Drunkeness that is the horrible <qex>sepulture</qex> of man's
reason.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sequacious</ent>⟦br⟧
